events.name: Networking for digital professionals
events.description:
Fancy a drink at the end of the week? or just want a relaxed quiet place to hang out with other like-minded digital professional, traveller, entrepreneur, student to share ideas or exchange resources?

Friday Night Social is absolutely free, and you are also welcome to invite and bring your friends!

The focus is on share ideas and exchange resources. However, if you want to party later on in the night that's fine also! We have discounted or free VIP nightclub entrance.

GDG | Edinburgh

events.name: Google Study Jam 2018 | Mobile Sites Certification
events.description:
Google Study Jam aims at demonstrating an understanding of basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development.

The Study Jams objective is to raise the technical proficiency of global community members through the highest possible course completion rate. GDG Edinburgh's study jam focus on completing a course, but some jams may focus mastering a skill or product area.

▬▬▬ Agenda ▬▬▬

15:00 pm: Welcome & Introduction
15:15 pm: Mobile Web Labs (Chapter 01)
16:00 pm: How to improve mobile site speed
16:45 pm: Break
17:00 pm: Mobile Web Labs (Chapter 02)
17:30 pm: Creating an effective mobile UX strategy
18:30 pm: Advanced Web technologies
19:30 pm: Break
20:00 pm: Online Exam
21:00 pm: Study jam event ends

▬▬▬ Mobile Site Certification ▬▬▬

A Mobile Site Certificate will be awarded to successful students that pass the exam, the credential will be listed on a Google Partners page and also provided as a printable certificate.

This study jam session by the Google Developers Edinburgh community will include learning about key technologies like mobile speed, PWA, AMP and web payments, followed by a 90 minute (multiple choice) professional accreditation exam offered by Google.

Location:
The event location will be announced soon.

Registration:
By clicking on "Going" on this Meetup event, you'll be added automatically to the attendees' list.

Successful completion of the exam gives you a professional accreditation from Google that shows you have proficiency in basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development.

▬▬▬ GDG Edinburgh Study Jams ▬▬▬

What is Mobile Site Certification?
A professional accreditation that Google offers to individuals who demonstrate an understanding of basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development.

⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯
About the Mobile Sites certification assessment:
https://support.google.com/partners/answer/7358899
⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯

Benefits:
✔ Content provided by Google Developers
✔ Accreditation (badges) from Google for your professional profile
✔ Community support that will ensure you get to the finish line
✔ Early alerts (via Meetup, Slack) to relevant resources/promotions to level up further

An email will be sent out from GDG Edinburgh in the week prior to the event with additional details. Please white-list these email addresses so your Spam Filters don't suppress it.

Requirements:
Bring a Laptop, Mac or Chromebook! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.

⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯

⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯

events.name: Edinburgh - GDG DevFest 2018
events.description:
Join us to discuss a wide array of topics ranging from multiple product areas such as Android, Firebase, Google Cloud Platform, Google Assistant, Flutter, machine learning with TensorFlow, to Mobile Web, Google Maps and many more Google related technologies.

An opportunity to lead the digital strategy, including tech entrepreneurship.

Edinburgh DevFest 2018 is a all day event connects with developers, coders, and designers about Google’s latest technologies. DevFest is a local and community organised developer conference with industry experts presenting on exciting topics including mobile, web, cloud, virtual reality, machine learning, and much more!

Google Developers Group | GDG - Edinburgh is for anyone interested in learning about the vast world of technologies that Google offers.

I/O Extended 2018 Edinburgh will be covering:
✔ Machine learning
✔ Cloud
✔ Mobile
✔ Web

Signup with meetup.com: meetup.com/edinburgh-developer/events/

▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬

You’ll also get the chance to network with experts from Google, University of Edinburgh, Edinburgh Napier University, Heriot-Watt University and become a part of the open and friendly community of the Google Developers Group (GDG - Edinburgh).

▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬ ▬

All skill levels are welcome to come join us in learning, teaching, and networking with others.

▬ ▬ ▬ Get Involved! ▬ ▬ ▬
While no two events will be precisely alike, all events will, at its core, be powered by a shared belief that when developers come together to exchange ideas, amazing things can happen.

▬ ▬ ▬ Get Social! ▬ ▬ ▬
We want to hear from you about your experience at Edinburgh's DevFest! Post to social media using DevFest 18. Tell us what you’ve learned and what you plan to do next!

▬ ▬ ▬ Be a Part of It! ▬ ▬ ▬
Are you interested in being a part of the Edinburgh Developer Festival Committee? Or interested in volunteering during DevFest Edinburgh? Message us to reach out regional lead for more information.

events.name: Google Hash Code 2019 | Edinburgh
events.description:
Welcome to our hub for the Google Hash Code. Sign ups for the Online Qualification round open in early January 2019. Registration is free of charge and will close on 26th February 2019 at 18:00 CET.

Hash Code is a team programming competition organised by GDG Edinburgh for students and industry professionals across the universities in Scotland's capital.

You pick your team and programming language, and Google picks an engineering problem for you to solve. For each round of the competition we’ll present a problem (see past problems here) and your team will write a program that generates a solution.

Top scoring teams will win cool Google prizes, because of course you can’t host a programming competition without something to work for!

Convinced!?

Sign Up for Hash Code here: https://g.co/hashcode/

The competition overview can be found here: https://hashcode.withgoogle.com/overview.html

Where We Meet? :

Appleton Tower (11 Crichton St, Edinburgh EH8 9LE)

Online qualification round on Thursday, 28 February 2019 from 18:30 to 22:30.

18:30 - The team system closes & the task is announced on our live stream.
18:45 - The competition starts & the problem statement is released on the Judge System. Take pictures and share them in our Google+ community.
10:30 - The scoreboard freezes in place for the rest of the contest to add suspense.
22:30 - The Judge System officially closes.
22:30 - Closing live stream to share highlights and announcement of top teams.

events.name: ML Workshop: Learn How to Build a State of the Art Machine Learning Model
events.description:
Hi all, GDG Edinburgh is back!

In this session, Marc Cohen, a Developer Advocate at Google, will provide some background on Machine Learning, how it works, how it's being used at Google, and how you can use it now to solve real world problems. Then we'll work on a lab exercise (so bring your laptop!). Together we'll see how to train and execute a deep neural network to recognize handwritten digits at better than 99% accuracy.

This event is co-organized by GDG Edinburgh and the Developer Student Club UoE (https://www.facebook.com/dscuoe/).

Students and non-students are welcome to join!

events.name: Community Speedrun Challenge #2: Kubernetes in the Google Cloud
events.description:
This is an online event. Register here - bit.ly/speedrunchallenge0220.

The Community Speedrun Challenge is a training program that will run in February where you’ll have the opportunity to join four Speedruns and get hands-on experience with tools like Kubernetes, Assistant, BigQuery our Cloud Run. Every Speedrun is open for a week to give you the ability to finish all labs in your best time, scoring more points and winning prizes.

Key info:
- This week's labs: Kubernetes Engine: Qwik Start, Introduction to Docker, Orchestrating the Cloud with Kubernetes, Managing Deployments Using Kubernetes Engine
- Timeframe: February 10th-16th
- Webinar with Sam Marder (Google)

More information & registration: bit.ly/speedrunchallenge0220

#SpeedrunChallenge2020

events.name: [IWD 2020] International Women's Day 2020

venue.name: Informatics Forum, The University of Edinburgh

events.description:
We are proud to be joining the Edinburgh University Hoppers Society as they celebrate their 15th birthday!

We offer a full day of fantastic activities enabling you to meet inspiring people and learn new skills. This year’s theme, "Reach for the Stars", invites you to imagine a world without limitations and acknowledge the importance of not giving up.

We have many opportunities to win amazing prizes and network with top-tier tech companies. Join our poster session (poster submission below!) for a chance to present the work you are most proud of to your peers, potential collaborators, and future employees, or ace our discussion round and learn more about future tech challenges.

The event is free and open for everyone - students, non-students, university staff, professionals (no matter the gender!)... you just need to register! ->> https://bit.ly/31NwTpf

AGENDA
9:00 GDG Edinburgh / Women Techmakers breakfast - fun challenges & prizes included!
10:00 Welcome from Hoppers
10:15 Keynote by Kate Ho, Hoppers' Founder and First President
11:30 Break
11:45 Lightning Talks

1. Toni Scullion from Dresscode
2. Nadia from HubSpot on the importance of side projects and
how to combine python and crocheting

13:00 Lunch and Poster Session with Prizes
14:00 Workshops (in parallel)

1. TensorFlow Workshop: Get started with ML Explainability and Trust (by us, GDG Edinburgh ❤)
2. HubSpot: How to build a React WebApp

16:00 "Future Challenges" - Discussion competition with tech leaders
17:00 Networking and Reception

REGISTRATION FORM
https://bit.ly/31NwTpf

POSTER COMPETITION SUBMISSION
https://bit.ly/38yccQR

More information on: https://edinburgh-hoppers.github.io/website/events

HIGHLIGHTS:
*Tensorflow Workshop: Get started with ML Explainability and Trust*
In this workshop designed for IWD 2020 by the Tensor Flow and PAIR teams at Google, participants should will be able to:
- Discuss how UX and eng work together to design and build ML systems responsibly
- Begin training your own neural networks using TensorFlow in Colab
- Explore how you can help your users calibrate trust using the People + AI Guidebook

#IWD #IWD20 #IWD2020
